Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1} into 1-inch pieces. Roughly chop @parsley{¼%ounce}. (Refrigerate parsley, peas, and cream cheese until ready to use in Step 5.)

Open package of @diced chicken thighs{20%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. In a #medium bowl{} (large bowl for 8 servings), combine @flour{1%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Add chicken and toss until thoroughly coated.

Place chicken in an even layer in a #5- to 6-quart slow cooker{}. Add carrots, potatoes, onion, @celery salt{1%teaspoon}, @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{4}, and @hot water{3%cups} (6 cups for 8 servings); stir to combine.

Cover and cook on high until chicken is cooked through and veggies are tender, ~{4%hours}.

Once soup has cooked 4 hours, adjust rack to middle position (top and middle positions for 8 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 350 degrees.

Coat a #baking sheet{} (two baking sheets for 8) with @nonstick cooking spray{}. Separate @buttermilk biscuits{6%ounce} and cut into quarters; place biscuit pieces 1-2 inches apart on prepared #baking sheet{}.

Bake until golden brown, ~{10-13%minutes}. (For 8, divide biscuit pieces between two prepared sheets; bake on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through baking.)

When ready to serve, stir @peas{4%ounce}, @cream cheese{4%tablespoon}, and half the parsley into soup in #slow cooker{}.

Cook, uncovered, on high, stirring occasionally, until peas are heated through and cream cheese is thoroughly incorporated, ~{5-10%minutes} more. Taste and season generously with salt and pepper.

Divide soup between #bowls{} and top with remaining parsley.

Top each bowl with as many mini biscuits as you like and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.